  "response": "Here are some polite ways to decline a coffee invitation:\n\n1. Direct but kind approach:\n\u2022 \"I appreciate the offer, but I'm not interested.\"\n\u2022 \"Thank you, but I don't think it would work out.\"\n\n2. Soft letdown:\n\u2022 \"That's nice of you, but I'm pretty busy right now.\"\n\u2022 \"I'm flattered, but I'd prefer to keep things friendly.\"\n\n3. If you want to be extra gentle:\n\u2022 \"You seem really nice, but I don't think we're a good match.\"\n\u2022 \"I'm not looking to date/meet up right now.\"\n\nThe key is to be clear, respectful, and kind while setting a firm boundary.",
